"NONE","body":"hello, loving Storybook so far!

I want to use the Notes add on to display code alongside my notes (aka without importing from a separate `.md` file) but this involves the use of backticks. If I were to do this in a template literal that would fail, and `withNotes` currently doesn't support github flavored markdown (which has tilde versions of the backticks for this purpose). so for example this doesnt render as a code block:

```js
storiesOf('Notes', module)
  .addWithJSX(
    'with a WithService wrapper',
    withNotes(`
This demonstrates usage of Notes together with a WithService HOC (that uses a child render prop)

~~~js
<WithService service={exampleService}>
  {(itemList, onChange) => <Notes items={itemList} onChange={onChange} />}
</WithService>
~~~
    `)(() => (
      <WithService service={exampleService}>
        {(itemList, onChange) => <Notes items={itemList} onChange={onChange} />}
      </WithService>
    ))
  );
```

beacuse the ~ tildes are not recognized.

This is because we dont really do much processing in the [Notes addon source](https://github.com/storybooks/storybook/blob/master/addons/notes/src/register.js). I would like to propose using [react-markings](https://github.com/Thinkmill/react-markings) to add a richer inline markdown experience to the Notes addon.

Happy to do a PR for this but is this something that you'd like?"},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/storybooks/storybook/issues/comments/364143348","html_url":"https://github.com/storybooks/storybook/issues/2916#issuecomment-364143348","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/storybooks/storybook/issues/2916","id":364143348,"user":{"login":"tsiq-swyx","id":35976578,"avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/35976578?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx","html_url":"https://github.com/tsiq-swyx","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tsiq-swyx/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2018-02-08T15:17:28Z","updated_at":"2018-02-08T15:17:28Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"hey Hypnosphi!

so i finally had time to look at the code.

i think instead of using marksy i could just directly use `marked`. so i just put this in `addons/notes/src/index.js`:

```js
import marked from 'marked';


export const withNotesGfm = text => { // dont conflict with withNotes for now
  const channel = addons.getChannel();

  return getStory => context => {
    // send the notes to the channel before the story is rendered
    channel.emit('storybook/notes/add_notes', marked(text));
    return getStory(context);
  };
};
```

what do you think about that? would be pretty simple.

the usage would look like this:

```js
storiesOf('Notes', module)
  .addWithJSX(
    'with a WithService wrapper',
    withNotesGfm(`
This demonstrates usage of Notes together with a WithService HOC (that uses a child render prop)

~~~js
<WithService service={exampleService}>
  {(itemList, onChange) => <Notes items={itemList} onChange={onChange} />}
</WithService>
~~~
    `)(() => (
      <WithService service={exampleService}>
        {(itemList, onChange) => <Notes items={itemList} onChange={onChange} />}
      </WithService>
    ))
  );
```

and this would render with the codeblock like a github flavored markdown would."}}

